We're working hard
to fill the sleigh

01:50.263 --> 01:52.078
So Santa Claus can leave

01:52.432 --> 01:55.393
Each year you see
You can depend on me

01:57.020 --> 02:01.389
We'll make the perfect Christmas toy
For evey girl and boy

02:05.777 --> 02:07.665
Happy Birthday, Santa dear

02:08.573 --> 02:11.315
Sixteen hundred special years with you

02:11.618 --> 02:13.495
How fast the seasons flew

02:15.663 --> 02:17.895
Make a wish and blow them out

02:18.122 --> 02:20.553
Celebrate a life about good cheer

02:21.334 --> 02:23.025
Here's to another year

02:26.882 --> 02:28.279
Thank you, eveyone!

02:30.803 --> 02:31.762
What a cake!

02:32.472 --> 02:33.921
Make a wish, Santa!

02:40.397 --> 02:43.128
- May l have this dance?
- Why, yes.

03:03.543 --> 03:05.190
Special delivey, Santa.

03:05.336 --> 03:06.473
A gift for me?

03:10.800 --> 03:13.355
Just arrived by North Pole Express.

03:13.553 --> 03:15.421
lt's from the Big Apple.

03:16.181 --> 03:17.390
''Dear Mr Claus:

03:20.226 --> 03:24.606
l regret to inform you of
Mr Hucklebuckle's recent passing.

03:28.109 --> 03:32.853
He explicitly asked me, as his
trusted attorney, to write to you

03:33.699 --> 03:38.276
and thank you for your
Ioyal friendship throughout the years.''

03:39.205 --> 03:39.923
Oh, dear.

03:42.540 --> 03:46.085
''Mr Hucklebuckle enjoyed
passing on your message

03:46.378 --> 03:48.495
to the children of New York.

03:50.215 --> 03:54.178
You taught him the true meaning
of Christmas spirit...

03:55.093 --> 03:57.815
...and the joy of a life of service.

04:00.351 --> 04:04.615
l've sent you the birthday
present from Mr Hucklebuckle...

04:07.357 --> 04:10.453
...that he had hoped
to give you himself.

04:12.778 --> 04:14.613
Sincerely... Mr Stewart.''

04:41.600 --> 04:45.927
Mr Hucklebuckle was a great
ambassador for the Santa Cause.

05:18.719 --> 05:19.074
Wow.

05:20.513 --> 05:21.963
Look at this place.

05:22.304 --> 05:26.247
- It's so nostalgic.
- Yeah, that's one word for it.

05:32.358 --> 05:35.381
l used to spend Christmas here as a kid.

05:37.529 --> 05:38.988
Nothing has changed.

05:39.239 --> 05:40.198
What's this?

05:43.993 --> 05:45.493
ls this a Santa chair?

05:45.494 --> 05:47.579
Grandpa used to
dress up for the kids.

05:47.580 --> 05:51.281
l'm sure the suit is
still around here somewhere.

05:51.376 --> 05:53.995
He loved the whole Christmas season.

06:01.220 --> 06:03.170
Mr Hucklebuckle, l presume.

06:04.513 --> 06:07.673
- l'm Mr Stewart.
- Actually, it's Huckle.

06:08.184 --> 06:09.936
l changed it years ago.

06:10.394 --> 06:12.512
And this must be Mrs Huckle.

06:13.981 --> 06:15.557
Please, call me Kate.

06:16.986 --> 06:19.112
My condolences for your loss.

06:21.114 --> 06:25.283
Your grandfather was more than a client,
he was a dear friend.

06:25.286 --> 06:26.923
l remember him fondly.

06:29.080 --> 06:32.301
So, as we were discussing
on the telephone,

06:32.584 --> 06:37.494
your grandfather left you the key
to the store to do as you wish.

06:38.506 --> 06:41.426
That's good. We're gonna put the
building on the market immediately.

06:41.427 --> 06:43.929
There is, however, one stipulation.

06:48.558 --> 06:53.479
You need to operate the store through
one Christmas season profitably

06:53.480 --> 06:56.034
before the deed can be transferred.

06:58.734 --> 07:01.527
We live in Los Angeles,
Mr Stewart, all right?

07:01.528 --> 07:04.364
And l'm a CPA with
a full roster of clients.

07:04.365 --> 07:06.117
And look at this place.

07:07.075 --> 07:08.952
Here, look at these toys.

07:10.580 --> 07:13.415
Kids don't want to play
with this stuff anymore. It's...

07:13.416 --> 07:14.581
lt's old-fashioned.

07:14.582 --> 07:19.212
Your grandfather used to say that
children's imaginations don't change.

07:19.213 --> 07:20.485
They're timeless.

07:21.006 --> 07:24.134
These toys even remind me
of my childhood.

07:24.135 --> 07:26.846
Back when they didn't
make video games.

07:26.847 --> 07:29.264
We'll keep the store open
through Christmas, Mr Stewart.

07:29.265 --> 07:32.163
Kate, we can't just pick up and leave.

07:33.436 --> 07:37.605
Your grandfather's apartment
on the upper level is open to you.

07:37.606 --> 07:42.216
Plenty of room, and l'm sure
your children will love it here.

07:45.365 --> 07:48.524
We haven't been blessed
with any children.

07:50.120 --> 07:50.891
l'm sory.

07:53.663 --> 07:56.333
l'll be back Christmas Day,
Mr Hucklebuckle.

07:56.334 --> 07:59.253
- Again, it's Huckle.
- Yes, of course.

08:07.261 --> 08:08.356
Happy Holidays.

08:10.805 --> 08:11.901
Mery Christmas.

08:32.035 --> 08:34.745
Don't wory, Quinn.
It'll be vey nice in there.

08:34.746 --> 08:38.134
There'll be other kids
for you to play with.

08:39.167 --> 08:39.825
Come on.

08:46.509 --> 08:46.801
OK.

08:54.557 --> 08:56.257
- Yes?
- Hi, Ms Stout?

08:57.686 --> 08:59.145
l believe you're expecting us.

08:59.146 --> 09:02.440
l'm Mrs Gibson from
Social Services and this...

09:02.441 --> 09:03.347
...is Quinn.

09:04.900 --> 09:07.686
Oh, yes, the new one.
Come right in.

09:15.411 --> 09:19.164
Oh, my. The place could use a little
Christmas cheer, don't you think?

09:19.166 --> 09:21.458
lf l got more money from the state,
maybe l could afford

09:21.459 --> 09:23.356
some Christmas decorations.

09:23.503 --> 09:26.840
Oh, here you go...
for Quinn's monthly care.

09:30.969 --> 09:34.253
Shall we introduce Quinn
to the other girls?

09:35.849 --> 09:40.239
They're studying. l take their
home schooling vey seriously.

09:42.272 --> 09:45.045
Quinn, l'll be back in a little bit.

09:46.651 --> 09:49.685
To make sure you've settled in.
Goodbye.

09:53.032 --> 09:53.751
Ms Stout.

10:10.216 --> 10:10.997
Sit there.

10:19.475 --> 10:22.644
l'll have someone show you around,
and more importantly,

10:22.645 --> 10:24.815
fill you in on all my rules.

10:27.148 --> 10:27.879
Willamina!

10:57.930 --> 10:58.660
Willamina!

11:05.188 --> 11:07.565
- Have you seen Willamina?
- No.

11:27.376 --> 11:29.190
Janie, where's Ms Stout?

11:31.964 --> 11:33.966
Where have you been, missy?

11:34.591 --> 11:37.010
l was just playing in the alley.

11:42.850 --> 11:47.229
New kid, much cuter than you,
and younger, l'm sure she'll go fast.

11:47.230 --> 11:49.562
l want you to show her around,
introduce her to the girls,

11:49.563 --> 11:51.899
and make sure she
understands my rules.

11:51.900 --> 11:55.237
Why do l always have
to show the new kids around?

11:55.238 --> 12:00.471
Because you're the oldest and l
hold you accountable for her behaviour.

12:02.244 --> 12:04.068
Willamina, this is Quinn.

12:17.675 --> 12:18.217
Scared?

12:21.013 --> 12:22.754
You'll get used to it.

12:23.014 --> 12:25.192
And it's Will, not Willamina.

12:26.518 --> 12:28.874
Come on,
l'll show you around.

12:33.441 --> 12:36.944
- This is the living room.
- But where's the Christmas tree?

12:36.945 --> 12:40.823
Ms Stout can't stand Christmas,
so none of us are allowed to have it.

12:40.824 --> 12:44.672
No merriness, no festivity.
She confiscates any toys.

12:46.078 --> 12:49.654
And most of all, she hates
any kind of singing.

12:51.001 --> 12:52.700
Eveyone, this is Quinn.

12:53.253 --> 12:56.129
Quinn, that's Janie,
Meg, Taylor, and May.

12:56.130 --> 12:57.547
What happened to your parents?

12:57.548 --> 13:01.092
They didn't make it.
They had to go to heaven.

13:01.093 --> 13:04.679
Mine neither. Janie's too, but she still
thinks they're gonna come for her.

13:04.680 --> 13:07.348
They are gonna come for me.
You'll see.

13:07.349 --> 13:09.267
And maybe even before Christmas.

13:09.268 --> 13:13.354
Nobody's parents are coming for them.
That's why we're here, silly.

13:13.355 --> 13:15.649
Your only chance is to get adopted.

13:15.650 --> 13:17.913
- What's ''dopted?''
- Adopted.

13:19.821 --> 13:23.197
That's when a new mom and dad
think you're cute and take you home.

13:23.198 --> 13:26.661
They like little kids.
Not older ones like me.

13:28.452 --> 13:31.352
Come on, l'll show you where we sleep.

13:44.260 --> 13:48.013
Jenny just left, so l guess
this is your bed now.

13:52.353 --> 13:56.816
l'll let you settle in,
and l'll be back in a little bit.

14:34.895 --> 14:37.752
All right, Eli.
What was so important?

14:38.648 --> 14:41.651
Well, we all know you've been
feeling a little blue, sir,

14:41.652 --> 14:45.446
and l think with the help
of a little Christmas magic,

14:45.447 --> 14:47.136
we could cheer you up.

15:09.805 --> 15:10.711
My goodness!

15:13.058 --> 15:15.707
l guess he's going to need a name!

15:15.768 --> 15:17.602
He is yours to name, dear.

15:17.603 --> 15:20.315
l think l'm going to name you Paws.

15:21.649 --> 15:25.893
You and l are going to be
best friends for all eternity.

15:26.238 --> 15:30.325
- Eternity? How long is that?
- Why, forever, young pup!

15:46.925 --> 15:48.019
Yes, wonderful.

15:53.307 --> 15:54.391
Yes, vey nice.

16:08.904 --> 16:10.479
Take the reins, Paws!

16:15.619 --> 16:18.592
Easy! Here, let me help you there, Paws!

16:27.422 --> 16:31.801
Honey, this store has barely
broken even for the past 30 years.

16:31.802 --> 16:37.694
And what's curious is that Grandpa made
a profit of exactly one cent evey year.

16:39.434 --> 16:42.770
Well, l have a feeling your grandfather
was not in this for the money.

16:42.771 --> 16:44.940
Then why did he put
that stipulation in the will

16:44.941 --> 16:46.565
that we have to make
a profit over Christmas?

16:46.566 --> 16:47.640
l don't know.

16:47.694 --> 16:50.654
Maybe Grandpa Hucklebuckle wanted
to make sure the store was run properly.

16:50.655 --> 16:53.574
We need something to bring in customers.

16:55.534 --> 16:58.702
What about a store Santa?
Kids love to go see Santa.

16:58.703 --> 17:00.787
- Yes, a store Santa, of course.
- Yeah.

17:00.788 --> 17:04.040
That's a great idea!
Where do you get a store Santa?

17:04.041 --> 17:06.221
l don't know... the Internet?

17:20.810 --> 17:22.435
Who will kiss my head

17:27.857 --> 17:29.235
When l lie in bed

17:33.322 --> 17:35.251
And who will hold my hand

17:37.492 --> 17:38.889
Who will understand

17:40.996 --> 17:43.102
Who will sing my song to me

17:52.925 --> 17:54.614
Who will hold me tight

18:00.431 --> 18:01.995
ln the dark of night

18:06.230 --> 18:08.222
And who will brush my hair

18:10.315 --> 18:11.817
Rock me in my chair

18:14.363 --> 18:16.469
Who will sing my song to me

18:21.328 --> 18:23.434
Who will sing my song to me

18:27.918 --> 18:29.544
Now that you are gone

18:43.308 --> 18:45.424
What are you doing out here?

18:45.435 --> 18:49.010
You better get in here.
It's almost lights out!

18:57.946 --> 18:58.906
What's that?

18:59.071 --> 19:03.618
My mom's favourite Christmas decoration
from when she was a little girl.

19:03.619 --> 19:05.912
We used to hang it on the tree together.

19:05.913 --> 19:09.167
lt's nice. Don't let
Ms Stout see it, OK?

19:18.300 --> 19:21.396
- Don't let Ms Stout see what?
- Nothing.

19:28.143 --> 19:29.811
What are my rules about toys?

19:29.812 --> 19:32.021
- Hey, that's mine!
- Not anymore!

19:32.022 --> 19:34.942
- Please! You can't just...
- Watch me!

19:37.152 --> 19:39.779
l've got some errands to run.
Will, you're in charge.

19:39.780 --> 19:45.046
And the rest of you had better
be fast asleep by the time l get back.

19:52.208 --> 19:54.919
lt's OK, Janie.
We'll get it back.

19:56.839 --> 19:57.912
No, we won't.

19:58.090 --> 20:01.259
We both know where it's going.
It's never coming back.

20:01.260 --> 20:02.647
Where is it going?

20:23.781 --> 20:27.867
OK, sir, l've prepped the reindeer
for landing in Central Park.

20:27.868 --> 20:30.079
Ever since Mr Hucklebuckle's passing,

20:30.080 --> 20:33.081
Christmas spirit has been
out of whack in New York.

20:33.082 --> 20:35.959
You mo be careful down there
and stick together.

20:35.960 --> 20:39.087
l'll watch out for Santa.
That's what best friends are for!

20:39.088 --> 20:42.352
Don't you wory, my darling,
we'll be fine.

20:43.300 --> 20:46.177
We'll visit some ambassadors
for the Santa Cause,

20:46.178 --> 20:50.307
talk to the children and
be back in a Christmas minute.

20:52.392 --> 20:54.999
- l packed you a bag.
- Thank you.

20:55.188 --> 20:59.066
Your suit, hat, gloves,
and some of my sugarplum pie.

20:59.067 --> 21:02.893
And you seem to have forgotten
your North Pole pin.

21:04.905 --> 21:05.802
l love you.

21:06.908 --> 21:09.171
- Goodbye, Santa!
- Bye, Santa!

21:15.751 --> 21:19.160
Now Dasher, now Dancer,
now Prancer and Vixen,

21:19.586 --> 21:22.746
on Comet, on Cupid,
on Donner and Blitzen!

22:08.886 --> 22:10.095
Will? You awake?

22:14.765 --> 22:17.196
lt's just the incinerator, Quinn.

22:17.853 --> 22:21.064
Janie said Ms Stout
put her doll in there,

22:21.565 --> 22:26.163
and if we didn't behave
Ms Stout would put us in there, too.

22:29.405 --> 22:31.948
She's just saying that to scare us.

22:31.949 --> 22:36.194
Ms Stout is not gonna put
Janie or anyone else in there.

22:36.495 --> 22:37.998
Go back to bed, OK?

23:07.693 --> 23:10.665
Oh, there she is, Paws,
the grand lady.

23:11.240 --> 23:14.524
- The Statue of Libem.
- Wow! She's amazing.

23:19.913 --> 23:23.324
Whoa! Comet, our landing spot
is Central Park.

23:24.126 --> 23:27.234
- Put her down gently.
- All right, Santa.

23:37.932 --> 23:38.652
Wow! UFO.

23:45.398 --> 23:46.357
That's good.

23:49.401 --> 23:49.944
Well...

23:52.071 --> 23:54.313
OK, fellas, you get some rest.

23:55.075 --> 23:56.616
We'll be here
waiting for you, Santa.

23:56.618 --> 23:58.067
Yes, come on, Paws.

24:20.390 --> 24:21.111
Nice bag.

24:42.497 --> 24:45.218
l love the energy
of New York City.

24:45.749 --> 24:46.876
There's nothing like it.

24:46.877 --> 24:49.837
Wow, this is way huger
than the workshop.

24:49.838 --> 24:53.288
Now, Paws, New York City
is a great big place

24:53.466 --> 24:55.093
with a lot of people,

24:55.550 --> 24:59.440
and only those who believe
in the magic of Christmas

24:59.512 --> 25:02.682
can understand North Pole
animals like you.

25:04.436 --> 25:06.729
So you need to be vey careful.

25:10.358 --> 25:14.550
What the heck? Watch where
you're going, you old geezer!

25:16.987 --> 25:18.541
l'm so sory, ma'am.

25:19.783 --> 25:22.075
Here, let me help you with these.

25:22.076 --> 25:24.256
Just arrived in the big city.

25:25.789 --> 25:29.959
Stop your dog from yapping.
Shouldn't he be on a leash?

25:29.960 --> 25:32.753
Not eveyone
has the Christmas spirit, Paws.

25:32.754 --> 25:34.319
She's not vey jolly.

25:34.422 --> 25:37.758
Why don't you mind
your own beeswax, buster.

25:38.384 --> 25:39.480
Mery Christmas.

25:43.182 --> 25:46.634
- Madam, your hat!
- Don't wory. l'll get it.

25:47.644 --> 25:48.364
Paws! No!

25:49.604 --> 25:50.020
Stop!

25:53.524 --> 25:54.849
Did you see that?

25:57.278 --> 25:58.666
Santa! Are you OK?

26:00.615 --> 26:03.867
- Oh, no! Santa's hurt!
- That guy just got hit.

26:03.868 --> 26:05.328
Help, somebody help!

26:07.330 --> 26:10.040
Oh, Mr Elf, Mr Elf!
l need your assistance.

26:10.041 --> 26:11.553
Santa's really hurt!

26:12.669 --> 26:14.786
Oh, no!
He just walked out.

26:16.090 --> 26:18.882
- Anyone know first aid?
- l got this under control, sir.

26:18.883 --> 26:20.761
l'm a... paramedical guy.

26:28.852 --> 26:30.114
Mr Elf, wait up!

26:33.314 --> 26:35.650
Look, there's no need for you to
stick around. You can get outta here.

26:35.651 --> 26:41.010
All right, move along, eveybody!
Move along! There's nothing to see here!

26:42.115 --> 26:44.169
Get away from me, you mutt!

26:44.450 --> 26:48.620
l'm gonna have to report you to Eli,
Santa's head elf.

26:51.500 --> 26:52.886
What have we here?

26:53.918 --> 26:55.065
Nice, vey nice.

27:00.966 --> 27:01.383
Help!

27:04.928 --> 27:06.805
You all right there, bud?

27:07.432 --> 27:11.561
Gus saw your whole mishap.
Could say l saved your life.

27:11.894 --> 27:12.791
Where am l?

27:13.438 --> 27:16.296
New York City.
Manhattan. Ring a bell?

27:16.816 --> 27:20.028
All l hear is bells.
Jingle bells in fact.

27:20.945 --> 27:22.687
Come on, let's get up.

27:22.989 --> 27:25.169
Oh, no!
Which way was Santa?

27:26.283 --> 27:29.035
- Thank you for your assistance.
- Yeah.

27:29.036 --> 27:31.537
- Anyway you could direct me to...
- Yeah. No, no, l'm in...

27:31.538 --> 27:35.031
l'm in a bit of a hury, bud.
See you around.

27:35.042 --> 27:35.397
Bud?

27:39.755 --> 27:40.538
Excuse me?

27:42.423 --> 27:43.999
Pardon me? Pardon me?

27:44.050 --> 27:46.469
- We're in a rush.
- Excuse me?

27:47.137 --> 27:48.283
Excuse me? l...

27:49.599 --> 27:52.810
Excuse me?
l was hoping you could help me.

27:52.935 --> 27:55.853
You see, l don't quite
remember where l live,

27:55.854 --> 27:58.285
or anything else for that matter.

27:58.356 --> 28:03.194
Though l do have a vague recollection
that l was supposed to be heading north.

28:03.195 --> 28:05.438
Then just take the north line.

28:06.989 --> 28:11.484
Why, thank you for your assistance.
You're a fine young man.

28:11.579 --> 28:15.426
- Mery Christmas!
- Yeah, Mery Christmas to you, too.

28:18.418 --> 28:22.057
Can anyone help me?
l'm looking for Santa Claus.

28:25.885 --> 28:27.448
What do we got here?

28:33.098 --> 28:36.613
This whole night has been a bust.
It's just...

28:39.105 --> 28:41.368
- What is...?
- Mery Christmas.

28:42.108 --> 28:43.202
Happy Holidays!

28:45.111 --> 28:46.572
Hey, Mery Christmas.

28:47.781 --> 28:49.989
Thank you vey much.
Thank you.

28:49.990 --> 28:50.345
Hey!

28:52.494 --> 28:52.848
Hey!

28:56.455 --> 28:58.571
This is my turf, bud! Scram!

28:59.543 --> 29:01.836
- l don't want any trouble, l just...
- Leave the bell!

29:01.837 --> 29:03.953
- OK, OK, OK!
- Ho, ho, ho!

29:06.090 --> 29:07.289
Ho. Ho, ho, ho!

29:12.597 --> 29:15.652
Happy Christmas...
Happy Christmas to you.

29:46.505 --> 29:47.787
Hucklebuckle Toys?

29:49.343 --> 29:52.428
Well, the lady at the
Santa Claus agency laughed at me

29:52.429 --> 29:56.318
when l asked if they had
any available store Santas.

29:58.727 --> 30:02.428
l had no idea how
beautiful this store was. Look.

30:02.855 --> 30:07.288
Kate, just don't get too attached
to this place, all right?

30:07.400 --> 30:09.986
lt'll be up for sale
as soon as it's ours,

30:09.987 --> 30:12.697
and then we're gonna go back to LA.

30:12.698 --> 30:17.702
lt was kind of nice to have an extra
project to take my mind off it all.

30:17.703 --> 30:21.247
l was kind of dreading the
Christmas season without a child.

30:21.248 --> 30:23.125
l know, honey, come here.

30:26.588 --> 30:29.087
Come on. Let's call it a night, OK?

30:29.088 --> 30:31.205
- We had a big day.
- Yeah.

30:40.976 --> 30:41.893
Hucklebuckle.

31:01.078 --> 31:02.047
Good morning.

31:02.997 --> 31:04.270
Thank you. Hello.

31:05.541 --> 31:07.116
How are you? Morning.

31:35.364 --> 31:38.033
Hey, the agency must have found one.

31:40.076 --> 31:41.286
He's... perfect.

31:43.120 --> 31:46.956
Look at him with his beard,
and the kind eyes, and that belly.

31:46.957 --> 31:50.649
Yes. l guess l could
stand to lose a few pounds!

31:52.380 --> 31:54.756
And the laugh is pretty good.
Vey convincing.

31:54.757 --> 31:56.894
- Great job, honey!
- Well...

31:57.176 --> 31:57.655
Wow...

32:00.555 --> 32:02.806
What a beautiful place this is.

32:02.807 --> 32:06.258
Thank you. It's been
in our family for years.

32:06.810 --> 32:09.428
- So, can you start today?
- Start?

32:11.566 --> 32:13.871
You're looking for work, right?

32:14.736 --> 32:15.278
Well...

32:17.613 --> 32:19.490
More like a home, really.

32:21.116 --> 32:25.120
You see, l'm new in town and...
a little disoriented.

32:27.582 --> 32:29.386
l didn't get your name.

32:31.961 --> 32:32.743
My name...

32:37.925 --> 32:39.615
Bud. They call me Bud.

32:39.969 --> 32:44.305
Vey pleased to meet you, Bud.
l'm Kate. This is my husband, James.

32:44.306 --> 32:44.962
Hi, Bud.

32:46.809 --> 32:49.782
Well, what kind of
work is it, exactly?

32:50.854 --> 32:52.303
Oh, in-store Santa.

32:53.649 --> 32:56.006
You know, you talk to the kids,

32:56.152 --> 32:58.779
you ask them what they want
for Christmas, you listen.

32:58.780 --> 33:01.448
Oh, that sounds
like something l could handle.

33:01.449 --> 33:03.753
- Great!
- So, we have a deal.

33:03.994 --> 33:07.870
Bud, if you'd like the job,
and you need a place to stay,

33:07.872 --> 33:11.125
we do have a spare room
with a bed in it.

33:14.293 --> 33:16.411
Yeah, here, let me show you.

33:16.838 --> 33:21.258
l don't know if you have your own
or whatever, but if you don't mind,

33:21.259 --> 33:24.011
we would love for you to wear
my grandfather's old Santa suit.

33:24.012 --> 33:27.662
- Yeah, for good luck.
- Certainly, l don't mind!

33:28.850 --> 33:30.122
Great. All right.

33:31.227 --> 33:34.564
All right, the Santa suit
is in this closet.

33:35.148 --> 33:36.348
l hope it fits.

33:42.197 --> 33:44.084
Why, hello, Cindy Cramord!

33:46.494 --> 33:50.799
Oh, l'm sory. Must have been
a case of mistaken identity.

33:51.665 --> 33:53.187
Franklin, you animal!

33:53.709 --> 33:56.001
- Are we still on for Friday night?
- l'll call you.

33:56.002 --> 33:58.411
l've gotta go get my hair done.

34:07.805 --> 34:09.317
Where are you going?

34:11.810 --> 34:15.147
- Who says l'm going anywhere?
- Can l come?

34:16.188 --> 34:18.056
OK, but we have to hury.

34:19.692 --> 34:20.349
Come on.

34:26.866 --> 34:30.117
All right, Ms Stout takes
mo hours to get her hair done.

34:30.118 --> 34:32.663
l don't know why she bothers.
She looks like a hedgehog.

34:32.664 --> 34:34.050
What's a hedgehog?

35:12.410 --> 35:13.745
lt fits perfectly.

35:23.088 --> 35:25.809
l hope your grandpa's suit fits Bud.

35:27.468 --> 35:33.067
You know Grandpa Hucklebuckle used to
say that Santa himself gave it to him.

35:42.525 --> 35:43.787
Do l look funny?

35:45.861 --> 35:47.977
No. No. Bud, you look great.

35:49.699 --> 35:52.616
lf l wasn't an adult, l'd believe
you were Santa himself.

35:52.617 --> 35:55.619
l don't think you're
ever too old to believe.

35:55.620 --> 35:58.394
Why don't you ty the chair out, Bud?

36:04.296 --> 36:08.237
lsn't that the most beautiful bike
you've ever seen?

36:08.593 --> 36:13.326
- Is this Santa's workshop?
- No, silly, it's just a toy store.

36:14.597 --> 36:16.682
You have to have money to buy stuff.

36:16.683 --> 36:18.924
Will, look!
It's Santa Claus!

36:19.520 --> 36:23.263
He's not real. He's just here
to help sell toys.

36:29.070 --> 36:30.832
lt's rather comfortable.

36:33.866 --> 36:35.868
Ho, ho, ho, Mery Christmas!

36:46.631 --> 36:47.892
You can come in.

36:48.423 --> 36:51.133
l don't got any money
to buy toys.

36:53.594 --> 36:56.179
That's OK, sweetie.
What's your name?

36:56.180 --> 36:57.462
- Quinn.
- Quinn?

36:58.766 --> 37:01.425
Are you here with your mom and dad?

37:02.519 --> 37:04.084
They didn't make it.

37:05.523 --> 37:07.576
Then who are you here with?

37:10.069 --> 37:11.885
ls that your big sister?

37:13.364 --> 37:15.721
Do you wanna talk to Santa? OK.

37:16.201 --> 37:16.858
Come on.

37:20.204 --> 37:22.070
And who do we have here?

37:22.416 --> 37:23.500
This is Quinn.

37:25.794 --> 37:26.273
Quinn.

37:28.171 --> 37:29.798
That's a pretty name.

37:31.383 --> 37:34.968
Would you like to tell Santa
what you want for Christmas?

37:34.969 --> 37:36.232
Well, hop on up.

37:40.641 --> 37:43.415
Sory. l had to see if you were real.

37:43.727 --> 37:45.480
That's quite all right.

37:47.398 --> 37:50.818
So what would you like Santa
to get you for Christmas, little one?

37:50.819 --> 37:55.291
l'd like it if you could
give Will the bike in the window.

37:55.783 --> 37:59.785
She's really nice, even if
she doesn't believe in Santa.

37:59.786 --> 38:03.871
And the girls at the foster home
need something to cheer them up.

38:03.872 --> 38:05.812
Like a puppy or something.

38:06.084 --> 38:07.532
lsn't she adorable?

38:10.546 --> 38:12.840
Come on, Quinn, we have to go!

38:13.549 --> 38:18.461
We'll see what Santa can do
for your friend, Will, and the girls.

38:19.264 --> 38:21.150
Thank you. Mery Christmas!

38:21.722 --> 38:23.308
Mery Christmas, Quinn.

38:27.979 --> 38:30.273
l told you. Santa is not real.

38:30.608 --> 38:32.839
No, l pinched him. He's real.

38:34.152 --> 38:37.155
You'll see.
Whatever you asked for won't happen.

38:37.156 --> 38:40.826
My mom says Christmas wishes
come true if you believe.

38:40.827 --> 38:43.953
- Well, your mom was fibbing.
- Take it back!

38:43.954 --> 38:47.456
- What?
- Take back what you said about my mom.

38:47.457 --> 38:49.804
No, l won't! Santa is made-up.

38:52.172 --> 38:54.466
Bud? What did she ask you for?

38:54.672 --> 38:55.214
Well...

38:56.843 --> 39:01.303
She wanted me to get her friend, Will,
that red bike in the window.

39:01.304 --> 39:05.266
And a puppy to cheer up
the girls in the foster home.

39:05.267 --> 39:07.269
- She's an orphan?
- Yeah.

39:08.980 --> 39:11.355
Aren't you a little fluffy poodle?

39:11.356 --> 39:14.869
Hury up, laddies!
l'll take care of this lass.

39:18.571 --> 39:19.364
Disgusting!

39:20.490 --> 39:22.378
You filthy little poochie.

39:22.994 --> 39:23.765
Let's go.

39:29.333 --> 39:31.576
Get out of here, you mongrels!

39:33.337 --> 39:38.091
- Hey, those are my sausages!
- Maybe those dogs have seen Santa.

39:40.218 --> 39:41.302
Get back here!

39:55.192 --> 39:57.484
Hey, that wasn't vey nice of you guys.

39:57.485 --> 39:59.278
Go sniff a hydrant, meddler!

39:59.279 --> 40:02.375
Yeah, laddie, who
invited you to the pam?

40:02.448 --> 40:05.950
Allow me to introduce myself.
l'm Paws, from the North Pole.

40:05.951 --> 40:08.611
Yeah, mon,
and l be da tooth faiy.

40:10.247 --> 40:14.835
Listen, laddie, just because we're
street dogs doesn't mean we're daft.

40:14.836 --> 40:20.070
You're clearly another one of those
uptown dogs with that bonny collar.

40:21.216 --> 40:24.677
State your business, buster,
before l bite ya like a chew toy.

40:24.678 --> 40:26.720
l need help finding Santa Claus.

40:26.721 --> 40:29.557
You expect us to believe
you know the man himself?

40:29.558 --> 40:31.311
What's in it for us, pal?

40:31.312 --> 40:34.397
Well, l'm sure Santa Claus
will appreciate your help

40:34.398 --> 40:37.671
and may even take
you off the naughty list.

40:37.733 --> 40:38.702
Naughty list.

40:44.656 --> 40:45.198
Gotcha!

41:06.762 --> 41:08.525
- Help us, mon!
- Help!

41:17.649 --> 41:19.703
And where have you mo been?

41:21.026 --> 41:24.863
l was just showing Quinn
where to take out the garbage.

41:24.864 --> 41:29.076
Well, l find that vey interesting
seeing as how we burn all the trash...

41:29.077 --> 41:30.662
...in the incinerator.

41:31.536 --> 41:34.455
Your hair looks
really pretty, Ms Stout.

41:34.456 --> 41:36.333
- You don't say?
- Yeah.

41:36.960 --> 41:38.596
Yeah, like a hedgehog!

41:40.963 --> 41:42.891
But that's what you said.

41:46.008 --> 41:49.930
l think it's time we show Quinn
the consequences of breaking the rules.

41:49.931 --> 41:50.473
lnside!

41:51.930 --> 41:54.142
Willamina knows that
when you break the rules,

41:54.143 --> 41:58.147
you get to spend all night
down here in the basement.

42:03.818 --> 42:07.362
You don't wanna be locked
down here all night, do you?

42:07.363 --> 42:10.826
Well, good. l'm glad
we understand each other.

42:12.159 --> 42:15.987
You're staying here,
and no dinner for you, either.

42:33.514 --> 42:36.058
New kids always get me in trouble.

42:48.404 --> 42:51.741
All right, doggies.
Let's get you in lockup.

42:55.827 --> 42:57.111
Bursting bagpipes!

42:57.288 --> 43:00.031
- Help!
- The situation is dire, mon!

43:00.292 --> 43:02.887
Hang on, guys. l'll be right back.

43:08.924 --> 43:09.644
You mutt!

43:15.807 --> 43:17.433
Where did he go, mon?

43:20.435 --> 43:23.042
Paws, you gotta bust us outta here!

43:23.981 --> 43:25.254
Stand back, guys.

43:29.236 --> 43:30.737
Come on, guys! Quick!

43:30.738 --> 43:32.573
Let's run like da wind, mon!

43:32.574 --> 43:34.263
Let's bust this joint!

43:36.410 --> 43:39.257
- Get out of my way!
- Hey, watch it!

43:40.748 --> 43:45.053
- What's a matter with you people?
- Get out of the road!

43:49.424 --> 43:53.438
Dat was amazing! You really
are Santa Claus' dog, mon.

43:53.760 --> 43:56.304
And that means we
really are on the naughty list!

43:56.305 --> 43:59.172
Oh, yes, T-Money.
Multiple infractions.

43:59.474 --> 44:02.478
You did us a solid, mon.
You be cool with us.

44:02.479 --> 44:03.685
Now we're your peeps.

44:03.686 --> 44:06.271
We'll keep an eye
out for Santa. Fo' real.

44:06.272 --> 44:07.243
Thanks, guys.

44:07.441 --> 44:10.942
l hate to interrupt, but we've got
to get away from the dogcatcher.

44:10.943 --> 44:13.854
You go hide, Paws.
We got him covered.

44:21.038 --> 44:22.122
There you are!

44:30.796 --> 44:33.216
How am l ever
gonna find Santa?

44:37.513 --> 44:42.371
One leaf from the Silver Linden
and the nature badge is all mine!

44:50.232 --> 44:50.651
Whoa!

44:53.361 --> 44:55.862
Hey, kid, do you believe
in Santa Claus?

44:55.864 --> 44:58.741
- You can talk?
- We're from the North Pole.

44:58.742 --> 45:02.203
We can communicate with all creatures,
as long as you believe in Santa Claus.

45:02.204 --> 45:05.424
- l believe in Santa Claus.
- That's great!

45:05.541 --> 45:09.001
Look, we need a big favour. Santa's been
gone longer than we expected.

45:09.002 --> 45:11.879
We're worried about him.
Christmas is right around the corner.

45:11.880 --> 45:13.797
But if you're Santa's reindeer,

45:13.798 --> 45:16.926
why can't you just fly back
to the North Pole for help?

45:16.927 --> 45:20.054
We can't fly without the
Christmas magic in Santa's cystal,

45:20.055 --> 45:21.971
and we have no idea where he is.

45:21.972 --> 45:24.267
We need you to find Santa Claus for us.

45:24.268 --> 45:27.227
But there must be
a thousand Santas in New York!

45:27.228 --> 45:31.565
But there's only one real Santa Claus.
You'll know him when you find him.

45:31.566 --> 45:35.861
As a member of the 23rd Street
Junior Wilderness Adventurers,

45:35.862 --> 45:39.315
- l will do my level best, Mr...
- l'm Comet.

45:41.492 --> 45:44.466
- That's Dancer.
- Mr Comet, l'm Jimmy.

45:46.747 --> 45:49.219
That's my leader.
l have to go!

45:53.505 --> 45:54.705
l'm here! Here!

45:55.256 --> 45:58.382
Jimmy, Jimmy, Jimmy,
you gotta stay with the group.

45:58.383 --> 46:01.720
Now, come on. Let's go to the
Junior Wilderness Adventurer cave!

46:01.721 --> 46:05.569
Marching. Marching. One, mo, three,
one, mo, three...

46:11.647 --> 46:12.065
Help!

46:13.023 --> 46:13.440
Help!

46:14.317 --> 46:16.017
Has anybody seen Santa?

46:16.152 --> 46:18.154
Help! Santa? Where are you?

46:22.783 --> 46:24.296
Can anybody hear me?

46:32.709 --> 46:36.411
- Hey, have you seen Santa Claus?
- You're a dog!

46:50.728 --> 46:53.646
l've never met
a dog that talks before.

46:53.647 --> 46:56.773
- Where did you come from?
- l came from the North Pole.

46:56.774 --> 46:59.131
- My name's Paws.
- l'm Quinn.

46:59.444 --> 47:01.903
Does that mean
you know Santa Claus?

47:01.904 --> 47:03.865
Yeah! He's my best friend.

47:03.866 --> 47:06.784
But l can't find him and
l'm supposed to take care of him.

47:06.785 --> 47:09.882
Wow! He sure is quick
at granting wishes.

47:10.831 --> 47:15.000
l have to go. If l get caught out here,
l'll have to go to the basement.

47:15.001 --> 47:17.837
Can l come with you? l'm really lost.

47:18.047 --> 47:22.342
The lady here is mean, so we
have to hide you real good.

47:22.800 --> 47:24.551
Come on! Come on, Paws!

47:50.578 --> 47:55.739
We can sleep here tonight and l can
help you look for Santa tomorrow.

48:05.385 --> 48:08.315
- Good night, Paws.
- Good night, Quinn.

48:20.733 --> 48:22.318
- Thank you.
- Hello!

48:23.778 --> 48:25.655
And what's your name, young man?

48:25.656 --> 48:27.365
Braiden. Bratty Braiden.

48:28.282 --> 48:30.533
lt's what my brother
and sister call me.

48:30.534 --> 48:35.133
Well, l see a kind boy who
wants to bring joy to his family.

48:36.416 --> 48:38.188
- Really?
- Yes, really.

48:38.875 --> 48:44.048
Now what would you like to give your
brother and sister for Christmas?

48:44.715 --> 48:45.934
- Honey.
- What?

48:46.009 --> 48:49.095
Bud is so amazing. The kids
are just drawn to him.

48:49.096 --> 48:49.877
Excuse me.

48:50.805 --> 48:53.055
- Can you help me pick out a few toys?
- Sure.

48:53.056 --> 48:55.182
My friend, Alice, told me
all about your store.

48:55.183 --> 48:57.393
She was so impressed with your Santa.

48:57.396 --> 48:59.813
Said he got them all right into
the Christmas spirit.

48:59.814 --> 49:00.595
Thank you!

49:01.232 --> 49:04.401
And what would you like
for Christmas, Tatiana?

49:04.402 --> 49:06.320
- That on the left.
- Oh, yeah.

49:06.321 --> 49:09.489
- And that on the right.
- Those mo train tracks.

49:09.490 --> 49:12.241
Well, Santa will
see what he can do.

49:12.242 --> 49:13.338
Mery Christmas!

49:13.745 --> 49:15.267
- Excuse me?
- Yeah?

49:15.663 --> 49:18.582
- Hi, are you the owner?
- Yes, sir. How can l be of assistance?

49:18.583 --> 49:21.377
Just... your store Santa
was suggesting to my kid

49:21.378 --> 49:24.045
that he buy presents
for kids in need.

49:24.046 --> 49:25.880
Oh, l'm sory.
l'll have a word with him.

49:25.881 --> 49:28.258
No, that's great.
l just wanted to say

49:28.259 --> 49:31.594
that we love that your store gives
a free present to a needy child

49:31.595 --> 49:34.097
- with evey purchase.
- Excuse me.

49:34.390 --> 49:37.307
Kate, did you hear what
Bud is telling the children?

49:37.308 --> 49:39.144
Yes, and l think it
is such a good idea.

49:39.145 --> 49:42.794
- No, we can't afford that!
- Honey, look around.

49:49.279 --> 49:52.386
This place could use
some Christmas cheer.

49:55.785 --> 49:56.204
Paws!

49:59.122 --> 49:59.477
Wow!

50:01.751 --> 50:04.169
How did you get this stuff here?

50:19.559 --> 50:20.039
Quinn!

50:24.730 --> 50:26.784
What are you doing in here?

50:27.651 --> 50:31.134
Where did these Christmas
decorations come from?

50:35.075 --> 50:36.783
Where did you find this puppy?

50:36.784 --> 50:39.120
l didn't find him, he found me.

50:39.121 --> 50:42.634
He came from the North Pole
on Santa's sleigh.

50:43.959 --> 50:45.409
Paws, this is Will.

50:51.050 --> 50:52.966
Quinn, that dog can't bark in here.

50:52.967 --> 50:55.303
Do you have any idea how
much trouble we'll get in?

50:55.304 --> 50:58.014
But he's not barking,
he's talking!

50:58.015 --> 50:59.766
Quinn, dogs don't talk.

51:00.392 --> 51:05.063
She can't understand me, Quinn.
She's just not a believer yet.

51:08.399 --> 51:10.318
We need to help him, Will.

51:10.319 --> 51:13.154
We need to show him the way to Santa.

51:13.237 --> 51:14.802
We know where he is.

51:15.699 --> 51:19.817
Quinn, l told you that
Santa in the store is not real.

51:21.413 --> 51:25.166
Thank you, sir. It's going to a vey
needy cause. Thank you vey much!

51:25.167 --> 51:27.169
Ho, ho, ho! Mery Christmas!

51:29.796 --> 51:32.588
Ho, ho, ho!
Yes, sir, what can l do for you?

51:32.589 --> 51:35.384
Santa, sir,
are you the one and only?

51:35.385 --> 51:37.678
Sure, kid. You put money in that bag

51:37.679 --> 51:41.055
and l'll pretend to be
anyone you want me to be.

51:41.056 --> 51:43.058
Ho, ho, ho! Mery Christmas.

51:44.559 --> 51:46.603
Hey, you're still
on my nice list!

51:46.604 --> 51:49.481
And it's the little engine
that could here in New York City.

51:49.482 --> 51:52.858
This small toy store has gathered
quite the crowd of people.

51:52.859 --> 51:55.611
They've come here to experience
a little of what they're calling

51:55.612 --> 51:59.615
the true spirit of Christmas.
l'm here with Mr and Mrs Hucklebuckle.

51:59.616 --> 52:01.660
Actually, it's, uh, Huckle.
We shortened the name.

52:01.661 --> 52:05.996
So, why is eveyone coming to
Hucklebuckle Toys to meet your Santa?

52:05.997 --> 52:09.082
Well, of course, the real
Santa is busy in the North Pole,

52:09.083 --> 52:14.015
but our Santa, Bud, he... he inspires
the true spirit of Christmas.

52:15.008 --> 52:17.759
They also like our
Christmas Spirit Programme.

52:17.760 --> 52:21.512
Purchase a hundred dollars in toys,
and we gift a toy to a child in need.

52:21.513 --> 52:23.598
- Well, that's wonderful.
- Mery Christmas to you, too!

52:23.599 --> 52:26.308
- Bud! Bud, come here!
- Let's talk to Santa himself.

52:26.309 --> 52:27.768
- Yeah. Come here, Bud.
- Mery Christmas.

52:27.769 --> 52:30.458
- Santa!
- Hello, and Mery Christmas!

52:32.192 --> 52:34.985
Santa, the kids really seem to love you.

52:34.986 --> 52:38.904
With hundreds of toy store Santas
all across New York City,

52:38.905 --> 52:40.844
what makes you so special?

52:41.324 --> 52:45.703
Nothing really, l'm just an
ambassador for the Santa Cause.

52:46.622 --> 52:51.168
One of many spreading the Christmas
spirit to children around the world,

52:51.169 --> 52:53.418
reminding them of what's important.

52:53.419 --> 52:56.004
A little humble pie. How refreshing.

52:56.005 --> 52:59.300
Well, actually my favourite
is sugarplum pie.

53:02.055 --> 53:03.638
There you have it: sugarplum.

53:03.639 --> 53:05.099
Here in New York City.

53:05.100 --> 53:06.360
Bud, are you OK?

53:11.939 --> 53:14.649
- You sent for us, Mrs Claus?
- Yes, Eli.

53:14.650 --> 53:17.235
Santa and Paws should be home by now.

53:17.236 --> 53:19.153
We were just thinking the same thing.

